# Glitch Vercel operations

## Default path

- Normal deployment flow is GitHub push followed by Vercel auto deploy.
- Use direct CLI operations only when env vars, cron rollout, or urgent deployment control require it.

## Guardrails

- Read `.env.codex.local`, `.vercel/project.json`, and `apps/api/vercel.json` before acting.
- Never print, commit, or restate secret values from `.env.codex.local`.
- The repo root is linked to the API Vercel project unless intentionally changed.
- Cron schedules are source-controlled in `apps/api/vercel.json`.

## CLI notes

- On this Windows machine, prefer `cmd /c npx vercel ...` because raw `npx` in PowerShell may fail under execution policy.
- Use token-based, non-interactive commands.
- Summarize what changed without exposing secrets.
